<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
<a class="spoiler" href="/questions/363666-anyone-else-not-convinced-by-roque-s">This question contains spoilers...</a>
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[Anyone else not convinced by Roque's betrayal? I know it was set up, and it was to be expected. However it just doesn't quite make sense with the character. Roque is a poet, if anyone would stand with Darrow in his mission to blend the colors it would be him. I just don't see him reacting the way that he did and it smells like he is part of this to actually help Darrow. What do you guys think? <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
