    The betrayal makes sense to a certain degree. What makes absolutely NO sense is him siding with the woman who killed Quinn in the course of that betra<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">…more</a>
    The betrayal makes sense to a certain degree. What makes absolutely NO sense is him siding with the woman who killed Quinn in the course of that betrayal. <a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">(less)</a>
  
